  "playingCareerSummary": "Former Sri Lanka captain and one of the greatest batters of the modern era: 134 Tests (12,400 runs at 57.40), 404 ODIs (14,234 runs). Four consecutive World Cup centuries in 2015. Played for Kings XI Punjab (2008-2010), Deccan Chargers (2011-2012) and Sunrisers Hyderabad (2013-2015) in the IPL.",
  "bio": "Rajasthan Royals' most successful post-2008 coach. Initially joined as Director of Cricket Operations in 2021, then doubled as acting head coach after Andrew McDonald was let go. Took RR to the 2022 IPL final (their first in 14 years, lost to Gujarat Titans) and back to the playoffs in 2024. Made way for Rahul Dravid for IPL 2025 but returned for 2026 after Dravid's single-season stint — his second tenure. Working partnership with Trevor Penney, Shane Bond and Vikram Rathour defines the current RR coaching setup.",
